The R script runs as following.

- Merge the training and the test sets to create one data set and names them

- Extracts only the measurements on the mean and standard deviation for each measurement and names the variables with "subject","activity" and the feature names.

- Use descriptive activity names to name the activities in the data set.

- Appropriately labels the data set with descriptive variable names.

- Create a the final tidy data set with the average of each variable for each activity and each subject.

Final Dataset :- 

Subject:
30 volunteer which ranges from 1 to 30.

Activity:
Contains 6 factors with walking, walking upstairs, walking downstairs, sitting, standing and laying.

66 left variables:
They show the average of each variable, which is the mean or standard deviation in the 561-feature time and frequency 
domain variables, for each activity and each subject.
